Exercise 2.1 – Bootstrap Structure and Files

Bootstrap folder contains different folders like CSS, JS, and Icons. Each folder has its own purpose.

1. CSS Folder

The CSS folder contains Bootstrap styling files.

Example files:

bootstrap.css
bootstrap.min.css

These files are used to apply styles like:

colors
buttons
forms
layouts
responsive design

bootstrap.min.css is mostly used because it loads faster.

Example:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css">
2. JS Folder

The JS folder contains JavaScript files of Bootstrap.

Example files:

bootstrap.js
bootstrap.bundle.min.js

These files are used for interactive components like:

modal
navbar toggle
accordion
carousel
dropdown

Mostly we use:

<script src="bootstrap/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

because it already includes Popper.js.

3. Icons Folder

The Icons folder contains Bootstrap icons.

These icons are used in:

buttons
navigation bars
social media links
search icons

Example:

<i class="bi bi-search"></i>
Conclusion
CSS folder is used for styling.
JS folder is used for Bootstrap functionality.
Icons folder is used for adding icons to webpages.